Just visited my son at #CBAT. he apparently cried in the night looking at our picture. However, we got to play with a puzzle and then for to play outside for a bit. I have more hope.

@iamadopted Yes! I‚Äôm building my online village! If you have recommendations feel free to share. Im not usually so emotional. Just going on day 3 of our son being in a short term #CBAT placement. It‚Äôs just hard to not have my little boy with me.
However, I just feel that him being committed to #CBAT is going to label him as someone with mental health issues. Our society is not accepting of this. What does that mean for him and his future?

Another day we wait to see if a #CBAT placement opens up. Scariest thing to wait for. A bed to take your son for 1-3 weeks for evaluation. I fear more for when he is gone, what will happen to him? To me? To us? Our family?
